{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_75","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Atomic stage-commit durability**: snapshot-write failure still leaks a committed stage into durable history.\n   - Current: [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L338) appends `stage_completed` before the next snapshot write, and on snapshot-write failure at [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L388) it only removes the payload/artifact pair before calling `fail_run`. The comment at [`engine.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L374) explicitly acknowledges that the `stage_completed` journal entry remains. The regression test at [`workflow_engine_test.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L528) checks file rollback but does not assert journal rollback.\n   - Expected: A stage must not become durably visible until payload, artifact, `stage_completed`, and the next `run.json` snapshot are all committed together. If snapshot or journal persistence fails, there must be no visible payload/artifact pair and no `stage_completed` event at all.\n   - Reference: Loop 6 acceptance criteria “A stage is successful only after...” and “Failure invariants are explicit...”\n\n2. **Required CLI and Gherkin coverage**: the checked-in tests do not satisfy the acceptance criterion for public `run start` coverage.\n   - Current: The CLI `run start` section in [tests/cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L2127) covers happy path plus some rejections, but there is no CLI case for prompt-review-disabled `run start`, preflight failure with no mutation, or mid-stage failure without partial durable-history exposure. Unit coverage exists for some of that at [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L155) and [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L299), but the spec asked for CLI integration coverage. The Gherkin file has a stage-plan-only prompt-review scenario at [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature#L66) and a generic failure scenario at [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature#L99), not the requested public `run start` scenarios.\n   - Expected: Add CLI integration tests and matching Gherkin scenarios for prompt-review-disabled `run start`, preflight failure with zero mutation, and mid-stage failure with no exposed partial durable history.\n   - Reference: Loop 6 acceptance criterion “Add CLI integration and Gherkin coverage for...”\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Re-run `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` in a Rust-toolchain-enabled environment; `cargo` was not available in this reviewer environment, so this verdict is based on static inspection plus the checked-in tests.\n\n---"}}
