{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_50","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Stage-commit payload/artifact write failures leave the run in `running` state**\nCurrent: After `stage_entered` is durably recorded at [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L221) and the running snapshot is rewritten at [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L254), the payload/artifact write at [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L394) maps errors straight to `StageCommitFailed` and returns without calling `fail_run`. I reproduced this against a disposable workspace by forcing `history/payloads` to be a file: `run start` exited non-zero, `run.json` remained `status: \"running\"` with `active_run` still on `prompt_review`, and the journal stopped after `stage_entered`.\nExpected: Any failure after `stage_entered`, including payload/artifact persistence failure, must persist a failed run boundary (`status=failed`, `active_run=null`, terminal failure recorded) and halt later stages.\nReference: Loop 6 acceptance criteria “A stage is successful only after...” and “Failure invariants are explicit...”\n\n2. **Payload/artifact rollback is still best-effort, so uncommitted history can leak**\nCurrent: [fs.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs#L675) best-effort deletes the payload if artifact creation fails, and [fs.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs#L683) / [fs.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs#L699) swallow rollback deletion errors entirely. That means the engine cannot actually guarantee “no paired history record is visible” when cleanup itself fails.\nExpected: Make payload/artifact persistence truly atomic or propagate rollback failures so the engine can prevent or explicitly surface leaked durable history instead of silently continuing.\nReference: Loop 6 acceptance criteria “Persist both payload and rendered artifact atomically...” and “the stage remains uncommitted: no paired history record is visible...”\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add a failing `PayloadArtifactWritePort` test seam to [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs) and adapter-level rollback failure coverage to [adapter_contract_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/adapter_contract_test.rs). The current suite covers journal/snapshot failure paths, but not the payload/artifact write boundary that still violates the spec."}}
