{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs | sed -n '320,420p'\"","aggregated_output":"   320\t    let _ = store.commit_delete(base_dir, project_id);\n   321\t\n   322\t    Ok(())\n   323\t}\n   324\t\n   325\t/// Get run status for the active project.\n   326\tpub fn run_status(\n   327\t    run_port: &dyn RunSnapshotPort,\n   328\t    base_dir: &Path,\n   329\t    project_id: &ProjectId,\n   330\t) -> AppResult<RunStatusView> {\n   331\t    let snapshot = run_port.read_run_snapshot(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   332\t    Ok(queries::build_status_view(project_id.as_str(), &snapshot))\n   333\t}\n   334\t\n   335\t/// Get run history (durable only, no runtime logs).\n   336\tpub fn run_history(\n   337\t    journal_port: &dyn JournalStorePort,\n   338\t    artifact_port: &dyn ArtifactStorePort,\n   339\t    base_dir: &Path,\n   340\t    project_id: &ProjectId,\n   341\t) -> AppResult<RunHistoryView> {\n   342\t    let events = journal_port.read_journal(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   343\t    let payloads = artifact_port.list_payloads(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   344\t    let artifacts = artifact_port.list_artifacts(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   345\t\n   346\t    queries::validate_history_consistency(&payloads, &artifacts)?;\n   347\t\n   348\t    Ok(queries::build_history_view(\n   349\t        project_id.as_str(),\n   350\t        events,\n   351\t        payloads,\n   352\t        artifacts,\n   353\t    ))\n   354\t}\n   355\t\n   356\t/// Get run tail: durable history by default, with optional runtime logs.\n   357\tpub fn run_tail(\n   358\t    journal_port: &dyn JournalStorePort,\n   359\t    artifact_port: &dyn ArtifactStorePort,\n   360\t    log_port: &dyn RuntimeLogStorePort,\n   361\t    base_dir: &Path,\n   362\t    project_id: &ProjectId,\n   363\t    include_logs: bool,\n   364\t) -> AppResult<RunTailView> {\n   365\t    let events = journal_port.read_journal(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   366\t    let payloads = artifact_port.list_payloads(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   367\t    let artifacts = artifact_port.list_artifacts(base_dir, project_id)?;\n   368\t\n   369\t    queries::validate_history_consistency(&payloads, &artifacts)?;\n   370\t\n   371\t    let runtime_logs = if include_logs {\n   372\t        log_port.read_runtime_logs(base_dir, project_id)?\n   373\t    } else {\n   374\t        Vec::new()\n   375\t    };\n   376\t\n   377\t    Ok(queries::build_tail_view(\n   378\t        project_id.as_str(),\n   379\t        events,\n   380\t        payloads,\n   381\t        artifacts,\n   382\t        include_logs,\n   383\t        runtime_logs,\n   384\t    ))\n   385\t}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature | sed -n '1,260p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration\n     2\t  The `run start` command executes all stages of the standard flow preset\n     3\t  end-to-end using the workflow engine, persisting validated payloads,\n     4\t  rendered artifacts, journal events, and run snapshots at durable stage\n     5\t  boundaries.\n     6\t\n     7\t  # SC-START-001\n     8\t  Scenario: Happy path standard run completes all stages\n     9\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    10\t    And project \"alpha\" is selected as active\n    11\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    12\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    13\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    14\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    15\t    And the journal contains \"run_started\", \"stage_entered\", \"stage_completed\", and \"run_completed\" events\n    16\t    And payload and artifact records exist for all 8 standard stages\n    17\t\n    18\t  # SC-START-002\n    19\t  Scenario: Run start rejects non-standard flow preset\n    20\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"beta\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    21\t    And project \"beta\" is selected as active\n    22\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    23\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"not yet supported\"\n    24\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"not_started\")\n    25\t\n    26\t  # SC-START-003\n    27\t  Scenario: Run start rejects already-running project\n    28\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"gamma\" using flow \"standard\"\n    29\t    And project \"gamma\" is selected as active\n    30\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"running\" with an active run\n    31\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    32\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"not_started\"\n    33\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"running\")\n    34\t\n    35\t  # SC-START-004\n    36\t  Scenario: Run start rejects already-completed project\n    37\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    38\t    And project \"delta\" is selected as active\n    39\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    40\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    41\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"not_started\"\n    42\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"completed\")\n    43\t\n    44\t  # SC-START-005\n    45\t  Scenario: Run start validates workspace version before proceeding\n    46\t    Given a workspace with unsupported version\n    47\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    48\t    Then the command fails with error referencing workspace version\n    49\t    And no run state is mutated\n    50\t\n    51\t  # SC-START-006\n    52\t  Scenario: Run start requires an active project\n    53\t    Given an initialized workspace with no active project\n    54\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    55\t    Then the command fails with error referencing active project\n    56\t    And no run state is mutated\n    57\t\n    58\t  # SC-START-007\n    59\t  Scenario: Stage plan derives from flow definition with prompt_review enabled\n    60\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    61\t    And prompt_review.enabled is true (default)\n    62\t    When the stage plan is derived\n    63\t    Then the plan includes all 8 standard stages in canonical order\n    64\t    And the first stage is \"prompt_review\"\n    65\t\n    66\t  # SC-START-008\n    67\t  Scenario: Stage plan skips prompt_review when disabled\n    68\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    69\t    And prompt_review.enabled is false\n    70\t    When the stage plan is derived\n    71\t    Then the plan includes 7 stages (all except prompt_review)\n    72\t    And the first stage is \"planning\"\n    73\t\n    74\t  # SC-START-009\n    75\t  Scenario: Preflight checks validate all stages before any mutation\n    76\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    77\t    And the backend is unavailable\n    78\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    79\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"preflight\"\n    80\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"not_started\")\n    81\t    And the journal has no new events beyond project_created\n    82\t\n    83\t  # SC-START-010\n    84\t  Scenario: Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic\n    85\t    Given the standard flow stage sequence\n    86\t    Then each stage maps to exactly one backend role\n    87\t    And the mapping is consistent across invocations\n    88\t\n    89\t  # SC-START-011\n    90\t  Scenario: Atomic stage commit persists payload, artifact, journal event, and snapshot\n    91\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"hotel\" using flow \"standard\"\n    92\t    And the run has started and is executing stages\n    93\t    When a stage completes successfully\n    94\t    Then a payload record is written to history/payloads\n    95\t    And a matching artifact record is written to history/artifacts\n    96\t    And a stage_completed event is appended to the journal\n    97\t    And the run snapshot is updated with the next stage cursor\n    98\t\n    99\t  # SC-START-012\n   100\t  Scenario: Run failure records failure in journal and snapshot\n   101\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"india\" using flow \"standard\"\n   102\t    And a stage invocation fails during execution\n   103\t    When the engine handles the failure\n   104\t    Then a run_failed event is appended to the journal\n   105\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n   106\t    And the status_summary includes the failed stage name\n   107\t\n   108\t  # SC-START-013\n   109\t  Scenario: Runtime logs are best-effort and do not affect durable state\n   110\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"juliet\" using flow \"standard\"\n   111\t    And runtime log writes are failing\n   112\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   113\t    Then the command completes successfully despite log failures\n   114\t    And all durable state (journal, payloads, artifacts, snapshot) is correct\n   115\t\n   116\t  # SC-START-014\n   117\t  Scenario: Journal sequence numbers are monotonically increasing\n   118\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"kilo\" using flow \"standard\"\n   119\t    When the user runs \"run start\" and it completes\n   120\t    Then all journal events have strictly increasing sequence numbers\n   121\t    And no sequence gaps exist\n   122\t\n   123\t  # SC-START-015\n   124\t  Scenario: Run ID is unique per run invocation\n   125\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"lima\" using flow \"standard\"\n   126\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   127\t    Then the run_started event contains a run_id matching \"run-YYYYMMDDHHMMSS\" format\n   128\t    And the run_id is consistent across all events for this run\n   129\t\n   130\t  # SC-START-016\n   131\t  Scenario: Post-run queries work correctly after successful run\n   132\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"mike\" using flow \"standard\"\n   133\t    And the user has completed \"run start\" successfully\n   134\t    When the user runs \"run status\"\n   135\t    Then the output shows \"completed\"\n   136\t    When the user runs \"run history\"\n   137\t    Then the output includes all stage events and payload/artifact records\n   138\t\n   139\t  # SC-START-017\n   140\t  Scenario: Only standard flow is supported in this slice\n   141\t    Given an initialized workspace with projects using flows \"standard\", \"quick_dev\", \"docs_change\", \"ci_improvement\"\n   142\t    When the user runs \"run start\" for each project\n   143\t    Then only \"standard\" succeeds\n   144\t    And the others fail with \"not yet supported\" error\n   145\t\n   146\t  # SC-START-018\n   147\t  Scenario: Prompt-review-disabled run start completes with 7 stages\n   148\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"november\" using flow \"standard\"\n   149\t    And prompt_review.enabled is false\n   150\t    And project \"november\" is selected as active\n   151\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n   152\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   153\t    Then the command exits successfully\n   154\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n   155\t    And payload and artifact records exist for 7 stages (all except prompt_review)\n   156\t    And the journal contains no \"stage_entered\" or \"stage_completed\" events for \"prompt_review\"\n   157\t    And the first stage_entered event is for \"planning\"\n   158\t\n   159\t  # SC-START-019\n   160\t  Scenario: Preflight failure leaves all canonical state unchanged\n   161\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"oscar\" using flow \"standard\"\n   162\t    And project \"oscar\" is selected as active\n   163\t    And the backend is unavailable for preflight\n   164\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   165\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"preflight\"\n   166\t    And the run snapshot is byte-identical to its pre-run state\n   167\t    And the journal is byte-identical to its pre-run state\n   168\t    And no payload or artifact files exist\n   169\t    And no sessions were created or modified\n   170\t\n   171\t  # SC-START-020\n   172\t  Scenario: Mid-stage failure exposes no partial durable history\n   173\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"papa\" using flow \"standard\"\n   174\t    And project \"papa\" is selected as active\n   175\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n   176\t    And persistence will fail during the first stage commit\n   177\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   178\t    Then the command fails\n   179\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n   180\t    And no payload or artifact files exist for any stage\n   181\t    And no \"stage_completed\" event exists in the journal\n   182\t    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing the failed stage\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_36","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t#![forbid(unsafe_code)]\n     2\t\n     3\t//! Stage contract registry and deterministic evaluation pipeline.\n     4\t//!\n     5\t//! Every stage in every built-in flow preset resolves to exactly one\n     6\t//! [`StageContract`]. Contract evaluation enforces a fixed order:\n     7\t//!\n     8\t//! 1. **Schema validation** — deserialize raw JSON into the typed payload.\n     9\t//! 2. **Semantic validation** — apply domain rules to the typed payload.\n    10\t//! 3. **Rendering** — produce a deterministic Markdown artifact.\n    11\t//!\n    12\t//! On schema failure, semantic validation and rendering do not run.\n    13\t//! On domain failure, rendering does not run.\n    14\t//! On any failure, no success bundle is returned.\n    15\t\n    16\tuse schemars::schema::RootSchema;\n    17\t\n    18\tuse crate::shared::domain::StageId;\n    19\tuse crate::shared::error::ContractError;\n    20\t\n    21\tuse super::payloads::{ExecutionPayload, PlanningPayload, StagePayload, ValidationPayload};\n    22\tuse super::renderers;\n    23\t\n    24\t// ── Contract family ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    25\t\n    26\t/// Classifies a stage into one of three payload families.\n    27\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]\n    28\tpub enum ContractFamily {\n    29\t    /// prompt_review, planning, docs_plan, ci_plan\n    30\t    Planning,\n    31\t    /// implementation, plan_and_implement, apply_fixes, docs_update, ci_update\n    32\t    Execution,\n    33\t    /// qa, docs_validation, ci_validation, acceptance_qa, review, final_review,\n    34\t    /// completion_panel\n    35\t    Validation,\n    36\t}\n    37\t\n    38\t// ── Stage contract ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    39\t\n    40\t/// A stage contract binds a [`StageId`] to its payload family, schema,\n    41\t/// semantic validation rules, and renderer.\n    42\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\n    43\tpub struct StageContract {\n    44\t    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    45\t    pub family: ContractFamily,\n    46\t}\n    47\t\n    48\t/// Bundle of a validated payload and its rendered Markdown artifact.\n    49\t///\n    50\t/// Callers receive either a `ValidatedBundle` or an error — never one without\n    51\t/// the other. On any failure (schema, domain, or QA/review outcome), no bundle\n    52\t/// is returned.\n    53\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq)]\n    54\tpub struct ValidatedBundle {\n    55\t    pub payload: StagePayload,\n    56\t    pub artifact: String,\n    57\t}\n    58\t\n    59\t// ── Registry ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    60\t\n    61\t/// Look up the contract for a given stage. Every [`StageId`] variant resolves\n    62\t/// to exactly one contract.\n    63\tpub fn contract_for_stage(stage_id: StageId) -> StageContract {\n    64\t    let family = match stage_id {\n    65\t        StageId::PromptReview | StageId::Planning | StageId::DocsPlan | StageId::CiPlan => {\n    66\t            ContractFamily::Planning\n    67\t        }\n    68\t\n    69\t        StageId::Implementation\n    70\t        | StageId::PlanAndImplement\n    71\t        | StageId::ApplyFixes\n    72\t        | StageId::DocsUpdate\n    73\t        | StageId::CiUpdate => ContractFamily::Execution,\n    74\t\n    75\t        StageId::Qa\n    76\t        | StageId::DocsValidation\n    77\t        | StageId::CiValidation\n    78\t        | StageId::AcceptanceQa\n    79\t        | StageId::Review\n    80\t        | StageId::FinalReview\n    81\t        | StageId::CompletionPanel => ContractFamily::Validation,\n    82\t    };\n    83\t\n    84\t    StageContract { stage_id, family }\n    85\t}\n    86\t\n    87\t/// Return contracts for all stages, in [`StageId::ALL`] order.\n    88\tpub fn all_contracts() -> Vec<StageContract> {\n    89\t    StageId::ALL\n    90\t        .iter()\n    91\t        .map(|&id| contract_for_stage(id))\n    92\t        .collect()\n    93\t}\n    94\t\n    95\t// ── Contract implementation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    96\t\n    97\timpl StageContract {\n    98\t    /// Generate the JSON Schema for this contract's payload family.\n    99\t    pub fn json_schema(&self) -> RootSchema {\n   100\t        match self.family {\n   101\t            ContractFamily::Planning => schemars::schema_for!(PlanningPayload),\n   102\t            ContractFamily::Execution => schemars::schema_for!(ExecutionPayload),\n   103\t            ContractFamily::Validation => schemars::schema_for!(ValidationPayload),\n   104\t        }\n   105\t    }\n   106\t\n   107\t    /// Evaluate a raw JSON value through the full contract pipeline.\n   108\t    ///\n   109\t    /// Schema validation → semantic validation → outcome check → rendering.\n   110\t    ///\n   111\t    /// Returns [`ValidatedBundle`] on success or a [`ContractError`] on any\n   112\t    /// failure. Non-passing QA/review outcomes are errors classified as\n   113\t    /// [`FailureClass::QaReviewOutcomeFailure`] — no success bundle is returned.\n   114\t    pub fn evaluate(&self, raw_json: &serde_json::Value) -> Result<ValidatedBundle, ContractError> {\n   115\t        // Step 1: Schema validation (deserialization into typed payload).\n   116\t        let payload = self.validate_schema(raw_json)?;\n   117\t\n   118\t        // Step 2: Semantic / domain validation.\n   119\t        self.validate_semantics(&payload)?;\n   120\t\n   121\t        // Step 3: Non-passing QA/review outcome check (before rendering).\n   122\t        self.check_outcome(&payload)?;\n   123\t\n   124\t        // Step 4: Deterministic Markdown rendering (only on full success).\n   125\t        let artifact = self.render(&payload);\n   126\t\n   127\t        Ok(ValidatedBundle { payload, artifact })\n   128\t    }\n   129\t\n   130\t    // ── Private helpers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   131\t\n   132\t    fn validate_schema(&self, raw: &serde_json::Value) -> Result<StagePayload, ContractError> {\n   133\t        match self.family {\n   134\t            ContractFamily::Planning => {\n   135\t                let p: PlanningPayload = serde_json::from_value(raw.clone()).map_err(|e| {\n   136\t                    ContractError::SchemaValidation {\n   137\t                        stage_id: self.stage_id,\n   138\t                        details: e.to_string(),\n   139\t                    }\n   140\t                })?;\n   141\t                Ok(StagePayload::Planning(p))\n   142\t            }\n   143\t            ContractFamily::Execution => {\n   144\t                let p: ExecutionPayload = serde_json::from_value(raw.clone()).map_err(|e| {\n   145\t                    ContractError::SchemaValidation {\n   146\t                        stage_id: self.stage_id,\n   147\t                        details: e.to_string(),\n   148\t                    }\n   149\t                })?;\n   150\t                Ok(StagePayload::Execution(p))\n   151\t            }\n   152\t            ContractFamily::Validation => {\n   153\t                let p: ValidationPayload = serde_json::from_value(raw.clone()).map_err(|e| {\n   154\t                    ContractError::SchemaValidation {\n   155\t                        stage_id: self.stage_id,\n   156\t                        details: e.to_string(),\n   157\t                    }\n   158\t                })?;\n   159\t                Ok(StagePayload::Validation(p))\n   160\t            }\n   161\t        }\n   162\t    }\n   163\t\n   164\t    fn validate_semantics(&self, payload: &StagePayload) -> Result<(), ContractError> {\n   165\t        match payload {\n   166\t            StagePayload::Planning(p) => {\n   167\t                let mut errors = Vec::new();\n   168\t                if p.problem_framing.trim().is_empty() {\n   169\t                    errors.push(\"problem_framing must not be empty\".to_string());\n   170\t                }\n   171\t                if p.proposed_work.is_empty() {\n   172\t                    errors.push(\"proposed_work must contain at least one item\".to_string());\n   173\t                }\n   174\t                for (i, item) in p.proposed_work.iter().enumerate() {\n   175\t                    if item.order == 0 {\n   176\t                        errors.push(format!(\"proposed_work[{i}].order must be positive\"));\n   177\t                    }\n   178\t                }\n   179\t                if !errors.is_empty() {\n   180\t                    return Err(ContractError::DomainValidation {\n   181\t                        stage_id: self.stage_id,\n   182\t                        details: errors.join(\"; \"),\n   183\t                    });\n   184\t                }\n   185\t            }\n   186\t            StagePayload::Execution(p) => {\n   187\t                let mut errors = Vec::new();\n   188\t                if p.change_summary.trim().is_empty() {\n   189\t                    errors.push(\"change_summary must not be empty\".to_string());\n   190\t                }\n   191\t                if p.steps.is_empty() {\n   192\t                    errors.push(\"steps must contain at least one item\".to_string());\n   193\t                }\n   194\t                for (i, step) in p.steps.iter().enumerate() {\n   195\t                    if step.order == 0 {\n   196\t                        errors.push(format!(\"steps[{i}].order must be positive\"));\n   197\t                    }\n   198\t                }\n   199\t                if !errors.is_empty() {\n   200\t                    return Err(ContractError::DomainValidation {\n   201\t                        stage_id: self.stage_id,\n   202\t                        details: errors.join(\"; \"),\n   203\t                    });\n   204\t                }\n   205\t            }\n   206\t            StagePayload::Validation(p) => {\n   207\t                if !p.outcome.is_passing() && p.follow_up_or_amendments.is_empty() {\n   208\t                    return Err(ContractError::DomainValidation {\n   209\t                        stage_id: self.stage_id,\n   210\t                        details: \"follow_up_or_amendments required when outcome is not approved\"\n   211\t                            .to_string(),\n   212\t                    });\n   213\t                }\n   214\t            }\n   215\t        }\n   216\t        Ok(())\n   217\t    }\n   218\t\n   219\t    fn render(&self, payload: &StagePayload) -> String {\n   220\t        match payload {\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
